<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,789,1609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,552,1041,1068]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Amended description – Male.</emphasis>
Tergum 10 divided mesally by epiproct and reduced cowl into two hemitergal lobes; lobes bearing dense matting of long setae (
<figureCitation box="[699,837,1078,1104]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[304,1281,174,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Alloperla stipitata, adult male epiproct. 23, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 800X; 24, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 1500X; 25, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3000X; 26, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsolateral, 3500X; 27, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X; 28, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3500X; 29, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 1500X; 30, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259323/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Figs. 23–24</figureCitation>
). Epiproct length (L) 
<quantity box="[1076,1165,1077,1105]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" unit="mm" value="150.0">150 µm</quantity>
, maximum width (
<collectionCode box="[1374,1429,1078,1104]" country="Netherlands" name="Museum Wasmann" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">MW</collectionCode>
) 
<quantity box="[151,227,1114,1141]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" unit="mm" value="62.0">62 µm</quantity>
, L:MW ratio = 2.4. In dorsal view the epiproct is widest in medial ½, tapering both anteriorly and distally (
<figureCitation box="[159,298,1150,1176]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[304,1281,174,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Alloperla stipitata, adult male epiproct. 23, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 800X; 24, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 1500X; 25, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3000X; 26, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsolateral, 3500X; 27, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X; 28, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3500X; 29, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 1500X; 30, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259323/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Figs. 23–24</figureCitation>
). The dorsal surface is covered by a dense matting of long hairs except for the anterior 1/5, which is entirely bare (
<figureCitation box="[309,448,1186,1213]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[304,1281,174,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Alloperla stipitata, adult male epiproct. 23, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 800X; 24, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 1500X; 25, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3000X; 26, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsolateral, 3500X; 27, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X; 28, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3500X; 29, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 1500X; 30, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259323/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Figs. 23–26</figureCitation>
). The apical notch is subtriangular and extends anteriorly and ventrally as a groove between paired, serrated apical margins (
<figureCitation box="[587,726,1221,1248]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[304,1281,174,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Alloperla stipitata, adult male epiproct. 23, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 800X; 24, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 1500X; 25, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3000X; 26, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsolateral, 3500X; 27, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X; 28, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3500X; 29, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 1500X; 30, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259323/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Figs. 25–28</figureCitation>
); 5 distinct teeth are present (
<figureCitation box="[1059,1198,1222,1248]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[304,1281,174,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Alloperla stipitata, adult male epiproct. 23, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 800X; 24, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 1500X; 25, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3000X; 26, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsolateral, 3500X; 27, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X; 28, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3500X; 29, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 1500X; 30, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259323/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Figs. 29–30</figureCitation>
); the serrated apex is linear ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[336,474,1258,1284]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[304,1281,174,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Alloperla stipitata, adult male epiproct. 23, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 800X; 24, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 1500X; 25, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3000X; 26, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsolateral, 3500X; 27, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X; 28, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3500X; 29, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 1500X; 30, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259323/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Figs. 29–30</figureCitation>
). In lateral view the epiproct is broadest medially (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1121,1258,1284]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[304,1281,174,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Alloperla stipitata, adult male epiproct. 23, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 800X; 24, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 1500X; 25, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3000X; 26, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsolateral, 3500X; 27, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X; 28, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3500X; 29, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 1500X; 30, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259323/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). The stem is slightly longer than the serrated apex and covered by a dense matting of long hairs except for a narrow bare band laterally near the hinge (
<figureCitation box="[272,357,1330,1356]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[304,1281,174,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Alloperla stipitata, adult male epiproct. 23, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 800X; 24, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 1500X; 25, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3000X; 26, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsolateral, 3500X; 27, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X; 28, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3500X; 29, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 1500X; 30, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259323/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). The lateral portion of the serrated apex is bare except for a single line of 5–6 hairs plus a few additional accessory hairs (
<figureCitation box="[456,540,1366,1392]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[304,1281,174,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[298,1289,166,1869]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Alloperla stipitata, adult male epiproct. 23, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 800X; 24, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsal view, 1500X; 25, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3000X; 26, Virginia, Fork Hollow, dorsolateral, 3500X; 27, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X; 28, Virginia, Fork Hollow, anterior view, 3500X; 29, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 1500X; 30, Virginia, Fork Hollow, lateral view, 3500X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259323/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,789,1609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Adult males (and females) are pale yellow in alcohol. The head lacks any darkened markings. The pronotum has a continuous pale yellow margin and the medial 75% of the segment is only slightly darker.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
